flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn label-request truth into authoritative supervision truth"]
    G2["Keep this path narrower than case-worthy selection, operational case creation, and label-request handoff"]
    G3["Answer where the platform makes the label authoritative, durable, and visible in the right temporal way for future review and learning"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw RTDL output, not operational case creation, and not merely that a label was requested somewhere"]
    E2["The entry is label-request or label-intake truth already handed off from the case side into the label boundary"]
    E3["The platform's own path language makes this boundary explicit: case or adjudication outcome -> label assertion -> append-only label commit -> label readback, maturity, and as-of visibility"]
    E4["The question this path answers is whether the platform produces trustworthy labels for later learning and review"]
    E5["So the entry is supervision intent ready to become authoritative label truth under one owned writer boundary"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Label-request or label-intake truth"]
    R2["Label store commit boundary"]
    R3["Append-only authoritative label commit"]
    R4["Readback, as-of, and maturity visibility"]
    R5["Downstream label-events handoff"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Case and adjudication lineage carried forward from the case side"]
    C2["Label assertion content with enough provenance to justify supervision truth"]
    C3["Idempotency and duplicate-safe commit identity"]
    C4["Conflict visibility and append-only label history"]
    C5["Temporal semantics: as-of visibility, maturity visibility, and future-label leakage protection"]
    C6["Downstream-readable label truth that later learning and reporting consumers can trust"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform does not treat a requested label as already authoritative"]
    L2["The label store is the writer boundary where supervision truth becomes authoritative"]
    L3["That truth is stronger than some row was written"]
    L4["It must be append-only, provenance-complete, idempotent, conflict-visible, and queryable by as-of and maturity"]
    L5["So this path is the closure point where supervision truth becomes durable and later usable rather than remaining an operational request"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["The copied baseline wired graph shows the label-store workload as a separate deployment from case management"]
    S2["The label store owns the authoritative label boundary rather than case management or a shared workflow state"]
    S3["The current wired graph gives this path a downstream handoff surface: the label-events topic"]
    S4["The label store publishes into that topic and later learning and reporting consumers read from that side of the network"]
    S5["So this is not only a database write; it is a real truth boundary with later consumers and visibility obligations"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["The platform needs labels that later consumers can trust as supervision truth rather than as ambiguous workflow residue"]
    Y2["That is why the docs insist label assertions must be append-only, idempotent, conflict-visible, provenance-complete, and queryable with temporal semantics"]
    Y3["The design also refuses to let case management own final label truth indirectly"]
    Y4["Instead, the label store closes the supervision boundary and exposes the result in a later-consumable form"]
    Y5["This is what keeps labels usable for review, replay, and learning without inventing truth after the fact"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The Case + Label plane contract requires authoritative labels with clear ownership boundaries"]
    X2["The label truth path contract requires append-only commit, idempotency, provenance completeness, conflict visibility, and queryability by as-of and maturity"]
    X3["The no-future-leakage law requires future-label leakage = 0 so label visibility has to obey real temporal semantics"]
    X4["The downstream-consumer contract matters too: the label-events handoff confirms this truth is intended for later learning and reporting consumers, not only the label store itself"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path adds a stricter supervision-truth boundary than a simpler case system would"]
    T2["That costs append-only commit discipline, idempotent write logic, conflict handling, provenance completeness, temporal query semantics, and explicit downstream publication"]
    T3["But that cost buys the ability to answer whether a label is authoritative, what case and lineage produced it, whether it was visible as-of the right time, whether it was mature enough for learning, and whether conflicting supervision truth was surfaced instead of silently overwritten"]
    T4["That is exactly the level of truth discipline a production fraud platform needs if labels are going to be used for audit, operator review, and later supervised learning"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the platform can still escalate RTDL outcomes, create cases, and even write label-like data somewhere"]
    N2["But it loses a clean answer to where supervision truth becomes authoritative"]
    N3["It loses a clean answer to whether label history is append-only or overwritten in place"]
    N4["It loses a clean answer to whether conflicts are surfaced or hidden"]
    N5["It loses a clean answer to whether later learning is reading temporally valid, mature supervision truth"]
    N6["That would weaken A immediately because the platform would have label-shaped data without a clear authoritative supervision boundary"]
    N7["The plane law rejects that by insisting on explicit label-store ownership plus durable, temporal, and downstream-visible label truth"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["Append-only authoritative label truth exists"]
    O2["Readback, as-of, and maturity visibility exist on that truth"]
    O3["The label-events handoff exposes the truth to later consumers"]
    O4["Owned outcome: authoritative, durable, temporally visible supervision truth"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>the platform has a distinct job for turning label-request truth into authoritative supervision truth"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the label store, not case management or a vague workflow layer, owns final label truth"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>this boundary is concretely seated in the separate label-store workload, its append-only commit surfaces, and the downstream label-events handoff"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>this path is governed by append-only commit, idempotency, conflict visibility, provenance completeness, as-of and maturity semantics, and future-label leakage at zero"]
    A5["Constraint-awareness claim:<br/>the platform already knows authoritative labels are useless if they are temporally vague, overwrite-prone, or invisible to later consumers, which is why those constraints are explicit in the path"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>the platform produces trustworthy supervision truth through an explicit label-store boundary rather than treating labels as just another mutable case artifact"]
  end

